Tips for Pregnant clients: 

Depending on how far they are, the client is unable to lay flat or on their stomachs. 

To be able to wax the legs, I like to elevate the top part of my bed so they are able to be in a half way sitting position. Then, I wax the fronts of the leg per usual. 

The back of the legs, I have the client bend their legs and get as much of the back as possible. Then I have them Lay on their side to get any missed hair. 

Usually with a leg wax I move quickly and run my hands post wax after large sections to calm the tingly pain sensation for the client. With pregnant clients, I do this more frequently as waxing during gestation can be more sensitive.

Soft wax can be applied to the skin using a stick or by using a roll on applicator. It adheres to both the hair and the skin, and is then removed by using a cloth or cotton fabric. 

Hard wax, on the other hand, is applied directly to the skin and allowed to cool and harden. It is then removed without the need for a cloth strip, and is often used for more sensitive areas, such as the face or bikini area. Hard wax tends to be less painful because it only adheres to the hair and not as much on the skin.

it’s as simple as:

1. Longer-lasting results: Waxing removes hair from the root, which means it takes longer for the hair to grow back compared to shaving. With waxing, you can enjoy smooth skin for up to several weeks, whereas shaving only provides a temporary solution as hair regrowth occurs within a few days.

2. Finer regrowth: When you wax regularly, you may notice that the regrowth is oftentimes finer and softer than when you shave. This is because repeated waxing weakens the hair follicles, resulting in less coarse and prickly regrowth. On the other hand, shaving can lead to stubble with thicker and blunter ends.

3. Reduced skin irritation: Waxing causes less irritation and redness compared to shaving. Shaving can sometimes result in razor burn, ingrown hairs, and skin sensitivity due to the friction caused by the razor. Waxing, when done correctly, is gentler on the skin and less likely to cause these issues. Additionally, waxing helps exfoliate the skin, leaving it smoother and more rejuvenated.
